I'm so fortunate to have veterans on my staff committed to serving #MA3 residents, especially fellow veterans who have sacrificed so much.

It was heartbreaking and infuriating to hear how last night's reporting regarding the President's view of their service is impacting them.

name: Trahan, Lori
message:
Without financial help, 50% of day care centers will go out of business. That means nearly 4.5 million young children who will not be able to go to daycare.

The President may not understand the damage this will do, but working moms do. They're living it.

name: Trahan, Lori
message:
By ending the #2020Census count a month early, this Administration is putting our vulnerable communities further at risk.

We need to make sure everyone gets counted so that communities across #MA3 get the resources they need. Visit https://t.co/h6LTatGeHy & complete your census!

name: Trahan, Lori
message: Are we really going to thank frontline workers with pink slips as they continue to risk their lives fighting #COVID19 & natural disasters at the same time? The Senate must deliver aid to protect essential public services. #DoYourJob #FundTheFrontLines
